# scopes.yaml — corpus scopes available to Phase 1 sessions.
#
# Each entry maps a human-facing scope label to a Milvus collection
# AND a Postgres table. At session start, the picker shows the list of
# `name`s; the chosen scope drives both the search layer's Milvus
# collection and the chunk-content lookup table for that session.
#
# `name` is BOTH the display label AND the stable wire key used in
# /api/session bodies and SessionSnapshot.scope. Renaming a `name`
# is a breaking change for in-flight client links — don't rename
# casually once a deployment is live.
#
# `milvus_collection` (required) is the Milvus collection used for
# retrieval. `postgres_table` (required) is the Postgres table used
# for chunk-content lookups (Phase 3 rubric judge + the `/api/expand`
# endpoint). There is no global default in `config.yaml` for either —
# every scope MUST declare both.
#
# This file is the committed template. Copy to `scopes.yaml` (which
# is gitignored) to add your real scopes; the loader falls back to this
# file when `scopes.yaml` is absent so a fresh checkout still boots.
# DEKA_SCOPES_FILE env var overrides the file path at load time.
#
# TODO: replace the placeholder below with the real scopes for your deployment.
scopes:
  - name: "Sales Chat"
    description: "Sales chat transcripts (placeholder — replace before deploy)"
    milvus_collection: sales_chat_chunks
    postgres_table: sales_chat_chunks
